In 1683, Qing Dynasty forces (1644–1912) took control of the western and northern coastal areas of Taiwan and declared Taiwan as a province of the Qing Empire in 1885.
In 1895, after the defeat in the First Sino-Japanese War (1894-1895), the Qing government signed the Treaty of Shimonoseki, by which it ceding the Shimonoseki sovereignty over Japan to Japan, which ruled the island until 1945.
